$docker build -t <name> . #Build Image

$docker run -p <HostPort:containerPorts> ImageName # run with exposing ports 

$ docker volume create --name nexus-data  #create a volume 

$ docker docker volume ls  #list the volume 

$ docker volume inspect hello #Inspect the volume 

$ docker run -d -p 8081:8081 --name nexus -v nexus-data:/nexus-data sonatype/nexus3 #Run with mounting storage 

$docker ps

$docker exec -it 8914d509ee69  /bin/bash
create a file in the mount location and restart to check if the file is still there. 


Repository :
$ docker run -d -p 8081:8081 -p 8082:8082 --name nexus sonatype/nexus3:3.14.0 # also open port 8082

Log into the Nexus and create a new repository 
Repository --> docker--> HTTP connector port 8082

$docker login 127.0.0.1:8082

Create an image : example:  docker build -t 127.0.0.1:8082/gautam .

$docker push 127.0.0.1:8082/gautam:latest